-- Lacoste Aims for 10% Growth in 2012, CEO Chenut Tells Figaro
-- B y   M e l i s s a   P o z s g a y
-- 2012-03-06T06:53:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/lacoste-aims-for-10-growth-in-2012-ceo-chenut-tells-figaro.html
Lacoste SA, the French clothing
company known for its crocodile insignia, is aiming for growth
of 10 percent this year, Chief Executive Officer Christophe
Chenut said in an interview with Le Figaro.  Lacoste’s younger, urban line called Lacoste Live now
represents 10 percent of sales, the newspaper said. The company
aims to boost the share of its women’s collections to 25 or 30
percent of sales, from 20 percent currently, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Melissa Pozsgay at   mpozsgay@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
